thread.title: Aust dollar stronger at noon
thread.title_full: Aust dollar stronger at noon | Business Spectator

author: AAP
title: Aust dollar stronger at noon
text:
The Australian dollar is holding onto the gains made at the end of last week as hopes for a US interest rate rise this year start to fade.
At 12pm (AEDT) on Monday, the currency was trading at US73.26c, up from US72.85c on Friday.
BK Asset Management director of FX strategy Boris Schlossberg said signs in the past few weeks that the US economy is slowing have caused many to push out the timing of a Federal Reserve rate hike from late this year to early next year.
